Ok we can’t beg that white needs better EDH cards and then complain about the power level of good white EDH cards.
Sure - it’s the TYPE of white cards…we talk about card draw or ramp, not about cheating Planeswalkers into play.
Arena Rector is like an ironic wish from a genie.

White does not routinely draw cards or ramp mana, and even if it tries to, it’ll never be as good as the other colors. It will instead get effects that simulate card advantage in different ways. Like free walkers or cheating equip costs.
I give you Stolen Strategy for red - Red doesn’t typically draw cards, but WotC has found ways to give them a kind of flavorful card advantage option.
They rarely explore that with White.
Also, Rector isn’t card advantage, but selection, if anything.

If selection is their workaround for white card draw, so be it. Why can’t get card draw, it’s not in the colors, so they need to find different options. 

Honestly, the big solution with white and red in EDH is not something people will like. These colors are balanced in 1v1 by their speed. They’re so fast that giving them ramp or draw would give them too much power in both early and late game. Since I’m EDH your opponents have 120 life instead of just 20 that speed is rendered moot. One of the best ways to do justice to the colors would be to give them cards with the correct speed, and whose power scales appropriately for multiple opponents. 

In other words, Purphoros or Serra Ascendant. Those cards suck to play against but in all honestly they pack a punch that’s comparable to how it feels to play fast red/white in 1v1. The easiest solution to RW would be speed, ending the game before they even need to draw more cards. Folks may not like that realization, but that’s how the colors work in other formats.
White’s way to keep up is to drag folks down, ala [[Balance]]
